l_call'}], invalid_tool_calls=[], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 7818, 'output_tokens': 35, 'total_tokens': 7853, 'input_token_details': {}, 'output_token_details': {'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content='Link: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siddique_(director)\n\nPage: Siddique (director)\nSummary: Siddique Ismail (25 March 1955  – 8 August 2023) was an Indian film director, producer, screenwriter and actor who predominantly worked in Malayalam cinema. He made his directorial debut with the Malayalam film Ramji Rao Speaking (1989). His screenwriting debut came with the Malayalam film Pappan Priyappetta Pappan (1986). His final film was Big Brother (2020).\n\nPage: Hari (director)\nSummary: Harikrishnan is an Indian film director and screenwriter who works in Tamil cinema. He is known for directing action and masala films. Hari made his directorial debut with Thamizh (2002) and went on to direct films such as Saamy (2003), Kovil (2004), Ayya (2005), Thaamirabharani (2007), Vel (2007), and the Singam film series (2010-2017). He mostly directs Coimbatore, Dindigul, Tenkasi and Thoothukudi-Tirunelveli district based movies.\n\nPage: Rohit Dhawan\nSummary: Rohit Dhawan (born 26 December 1983) is an Indian filmmaker and screenwriter. He is the elder son of filmmaker David Dhawan, and the brother of Varun Dhawan.\n\n--- [Automatic Crawl of Top Result: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siddique_(director] ---\nTitle: Siddique (director - Wikipedia\n\nURL Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siddique_(director\n\nWarning: Target URL returned error 404: Not Found\n\nMarkdown Content:\nPage contents not supported in other languages.\n\n*   [Article](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Siddique_(director&action=edit&redlink=1 "View the content page (page does not exist) [alt-c]")\n*   [Talk](https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Siddique_(director&action=edit&redlink=1 "Discuss improvements to the content page (page does not exist) [alt-t]")\n\nTools\n\nActions\